# kioku vault

This is your Claude Code long-term memory vault, managed by [kioku](https://github.com/hir4ta/kioku).

## What goes where

- `working/` — your **live workspace**. `focus.md`, `next.md`, `unresolved.md` are auto-injected into every new Claude session.
- `episodic/sessions/` — auto-generated session summaries. **Read these, don't edit** (kioku will re-render on next consolidation).
- `semantic/decisions/active/` — decisions currently in force. **Edit these freely** — they shape future Claude responses.
- `semantic/patterns/` `semantic/mistakes/` `semantic/preferences/` — knowledge layers.
- `procedural/skills/` `procedural/recipes/` — reusable how-tos.
- `projects/<slug>/` — project-specific memory. `focus.md` and `decisions/` mirror the global layout but scoped to one project.
- `compact-handover/` — auto-generated PreCompact hand-off. Don't edit.
- `_meta/dashboard.md` — Dataview-driven overview of the entire vault.

## How memory entries are structured

All entries follow the **MADR** (Markdown Architectural Decision Records) format:

1. **Title** with the decision/finding on the first line.
2. **Decision / TL;DR** right after the title (this is what chunk retrieval surfaces).
3. **Why** and **Consequences** bullets.
4. **Context** section **last** — only read if the reader needs background.

Frontmatter is required and validated against `memory.schema.json`. See the kioku repo `templates/` directory for examples (`decision.md.tmpl`, `session-summary.md.tmpl`, `pattern.md.tmpl`).

## Privacy

Mark content you don't want indexed with `<no-memory>...</no-memory>` or `<private>...</private>`. The `redact.py` layer strips these before any Voyage API call. Secret-shaped strings (API keys, JWTs, high-entropy tokens) are auto-detected and blocked even without explicit tagging.

## Working with this vault

- Open it in **Obsidian** to browse, edit, and search like any other vault.
- Run `kioku search <query>` to retrieve via hybrid (BM25 + Voyage embedding + rerank-2.5).
- Run `kioku status` to see what kioku injected into your most recent session.
- Run `kioku rebuild` if you bulk-edited files outside kioku and want the SQLite index regenerated.

## Trust model

Memories carry a `trust` frontmatter field:

- `high` — written by you, by hand, in this vault.
- `medium` — extracted by kioku from a Claude Code session you ran.
- `low` — imported from external sources (rare; never auto-injected without explicit opt-in).

`trust: low` records are stripped from injection by default. Override per-call with `kioku search --include-low-trust`.
